    "reviews_attribution": "運営者が確認した1,148件のレビューに基づく平均評価は4.9/5です。このページでは評価の概要のみを表示しています。",
    "unesco_fit_note": "unesco_fit=5 = 1 WHS (Seongsan Ilchulbong, inscribed 2007) + 1 Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity (Culture of Jeju Haenyeo, inscribed 2016, accessed via the Haenyeo Museum stop). Seongeup Folk Village is Korea's national folk heritage — NOT ユネスコ — and does not contribute to this score.",
    "_internal_competing_products_note": "Comp set (internal only): Southern ユネスコ sister product, same operator, $43/pax small-group rate as ceiling reference.",
    "competing_products": [
      "east-signature-nature-core",
      "jeju-grand-highlights-loop",
      "jeju-southern-top-unesco-spots-tour"
    ],
    "audit_summary": "East Jeju ユネスコ-focused loop covering 5 distinct ユネスコ heritage layers in one day: Olle Trail walking heritage (Hamdeok Course 19), Important Folklore Cultural Heritage (Seongeup Folk Village 1423 founding), Manjanggul-system lava tube (Ilchulland — ユネスコ-property adjacent), Triple ユネスコ Surtseyan tuff cone (Seongsan Ilchulbong), and ユネスコ Intangible Cultural Heritage of Humanity (Jeju Haenyeo Museum, 2016 inscription). ユネスコ-anchored counterpart to the signature-nature sister tour, which emphasizes Seolmundae Halmang mythology + Tadao Ando architecture instead.",
    "score_rationale": {
